Lands Cabinet Secretary Jacob Kaimenyi has urged aspirants to stop using land problems to campaign. He spoke on Monday outside Huduma Centre in Tharaka Nithi after a meeting at the county commissioner&rsquo;s office.The meeting discussed how to mobilise residents to register as voters in the final phase of mass listing, which started on Monday.Kaimenyi was with Fisheries PS Micheni Ntiba, Defence PS Kirimi Kaberia and Tharaka Nithi county commissioner Florence Amoit. &ldquo;Politicians should not use land as a campaign tool because the ministry has put in place enough, elaborate mechanisms to address land problems,&rdquo; Kaimenyi said.